OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FThe UK is drawing up plans to prepare
OL,8,Ffor worst-case scenario food shortages
OL,9,Fshould the Iran war continue into the
OL,10,Fsummer.
OL,12,FA leak of government plans, seen by
OL,13,FThe Times, shows senior officials from
OL,14,Fmultiple government departments have
OL,15,Fbeen examining the potential impact on
OL,16,FBritish industry should the Strait of
OL,17,FHormuz remain closed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FThough the war is not likely to lead
OL,8,Fto critical shortages, a reasonable
OL,9,Fworst-case scenario from leaked
OL,10,Fgovernment plans suggests there could
OL,11,Fbe less variety on supermarket shelves
OL,12,Fshould fighting continue.
OL,14,FCarbon dioxide (CO2) supplies would
OL,15,Falso be hit should the conflict last
OL,16,Finto the summer, according to the same
OL,17,Fleak, which would have an impact on
OL,18,Fthe storage of packaged meats and
OL,19,Fsalads, and on breweries, which use
OL,20,Fthe gas to make drinks fizzy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FThe Times reported the reasonable
OL,8,Fworst-case scenario saw CO2 supplies
OL,9,Ffalling to 18% of current levels.
OL,11,FThis scenario included a key UK plant
OL,12,Fsuffering a malfunction, reducing or
OL,13,Fhalting its production of the gas
OL,14,Fentirely, and high energy costs
OL,15,Fleading to a fall in production across
OL,16,FEurope of ammonia and fertiliser,
OL,17,Fwhich make CO2 as a by-product.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,FConcerns were also raised that this
OL,8,FCO2 shortage may coincide with the
OL,9,FWorld Cup, when demand for carbonated
OL,10,Fbeers is likely to be higher.
OL,12,FSpeaking on Thursday morning, Business
OL,13,FSecretary Peter Kye said the British
OL,14,Fpublic could be "reassured" that the
OL,15,Fgovernment was planning for these
OL,16,Fpotential scenarios.
OL,18,F"Scenario planning, by definition,
OL,19,Fmeans that we are looking into a
OL,20,Fvariety of different scenarios that
OL,21,Fmay or may not happen.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,F"People should go about their lives as
OL,8,Fnormal. If there are changes to that,
OL,9,Fwe will be upfront with the British
OL,10,Fpublic."
OL,12,FKyle drew attention to the additional
OL,13,Ffunding provided by the government to
OL,14,Freactivate the Ensus bioethanol plant,
OL,15,Fwhich makes CO2 as a by-product, in
OL,16,Forder to shore up supplies of the gas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1776409519
OL,3,CGovernment reportedly drawing up
OL,4,C'worst case scenario' plans for food
OL,5,Cshortages
OL,7,F"There are critical uses for CO2: MRI
OL,8,Fscanning, for example, water
OL,9,Fpurification; it's involved in our
OL,10,Fnuclear industry, our civil nuclear
OL,11,Fpower industry, some defensive uses
OL,12,Ffor it as well," he said.
OL,14,F"There's lots of needs for CO2, so
OL,15,Fthese are the reasons why I took it so
OL,16,Fseriously way back to six months ago,
OL,17,Fnot just in the last few weeks."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
